Arteta on Mari: &ldquo;I think he needs minutes, like Rob [Holding], like Ainsley [Maitland-Niles] &amp; Reiss [Nelson] as well. I think it was a good game for them [vs. #mcfc U23s] to get their fitness levels tested &amp; they trained today really well. They are all, I think, ready to play.&rdquo; <br />
<br />
Mikel Arteta on Kieran Tierney: &ldquo;He is much closer. He is evolving really well. He feels fit. He feels confident now. He&rsquo;s doing the stuff with contact, so hopefully we can have him soon. [Available for Monday?] As soon as I don&rsquo;t know when! Whenever we decide.&rdquo;

There are two Premier league clubs that have contacted Thomas Partey's representatives to inform them that they are willing to pay Partey's &euro;50m release clause. [<br />
@carrusel<br />
]<br />
<br />
Atletico Madrid want to tie Partey down to a new contract with a higher release clause but have had no luck so far. Atleti believe his clause is outdated and should be higher. The two clubs interested in Partey, have in the past, paid &euro;80m for defenders.
